INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2013-01-30 00:17:49','2013-01-30 00:17:49','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','publish','open','open','','hello-world','','','2013-01-30 00:17:49','2013-01-30 00:17:49','',0,'http://template.jobs.1stsocial.com.au/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(2,1,'2013-01-30 00:17:49','2013-01-30 00:17:49','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://template.jobs.1stsocial.com.au/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','publish','open','open','','sample-page','','','2013-01-30 00:17:49','2013-01-30 00:17:49','',0,'http://template.jobs.1stsocial.com.au/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2013-04-04 23:20:10','2013-04-04 23:20:10','','Application Link','','publish','open','open','','application-link','','','2013-04-04 23:20:10','2013-04-04 23:20:10','',0,'http://template.jobs.1stsocial.com.au/wp-types-group/application-link/',0,'wp-types-group','',0),(17,1,'2013-04-29 07:08:50','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2013-04-29 07:08:50','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://template.jobs.1stsocial.com.au/?p=17',0,'post','',0),(14,1,'2013-04-05 01:15:46','2013-04-05 01:15:46','Job 1 Desc','Job 1 Title','','publish','closed','closed','','job-1-title','','','2013-04-05 01:15:46','2013-04-05 01:15:46','',0,'http://template.jobs.1stsocial.com.au/?post_type=jobs&#038;p=14',0,'jobs','',0),(15,1,'2013-04-05 01:16:50','2013-04-05 01:16:50','Job 1 Desc','Job 1 Title','','inherit','open','open','','14-autosave','','','2013-04-05 01:16:50','2013-04-05 01:16:50','',14,'http://template.jobs.1stsocial.com.au/2013/04/05/14-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(16,2,'2013-04-05 06:06:10','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Project Engineer - 2 years experience ideally in waste water treatment process, needed for leader in design &amp; delivery of waste water solutions.\n<ul>\n	<li>Circa $70K plus super</li>\n	<li>Market Leader - water industry</li>\n	<li>Brisbane Office or work from home</li>\n</ul>\nOur client is a market leader in the manufacture of commercial scale water treatment and wastewater recycling systems. With activity in Australia and growth in overseas markets, they are entering a strong growth phase and are looking for the skills and aptitude of an experienced Project Engineer who enjoys the full circle process.\n\nYou will have 2+ years professional engineering design experience coupled with a degree in Mechanical Engineering. Your past experience may include exposure to the design of wastewater plants including process, hydraulic and mechanical/electrical components. An understanding of technical aspects of wastewater treatment in a variety of decentralized wastewater treatment technologies and water treatment technologies would be advantageous along with your ability to develop functional specifications for water and wastewater treatment systems. Your love of new technology will keep you interested in assessing new treatment technologies/processes and assisting in applying them to practical ecologically sustainable designs.\nReporting to the General Manager and working closely with a senior Engineer and small team of key staff, your main responsibilities will be Support to the team of onsite Treatment plant operators, trend analysis, identification of improved design/process and delivery of changes to standard product delivery whilst liaising with the client and coordinating all relevant subcontractors.\nYou will also conduct ongoing research and product/system development to meet evolving market opportunities and demands as well as continuous improvement focus across your areas of responsibility.\nYou will have excellent time management skills and the self discipline to ensure that you can manage the coordination of several projects concurrently. Attention to detail, initiative and accountability are all a must along with the flexibility to travel to remote sites\nIf you are looking for a role where you can make a difference, in a company that ismaking a difference - this is your next long term challenge.\nPlease click on the ‘Apply Now’ button below to submit your confidential application or telephone Suzanne Whitmarsh on (03) 8617 8110 for further information. Please see ‘Job Search\' on www.facebook.com/1stexecutive where you can apply and also register your details.','Project Engineer - Water','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2013-04-05 06:06:10','2013-04-05 06:06:10','',0,'http://template.jobs.1stsocial.com.au/?post_type=jobs&#038;p=16',0,'jobs','',0);
